<paragraph id="7A8ABEA6BF0EF7AFB629E9F258A2F5CF" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="EA2F06A016596C19512C9F31F4DEB1A6" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="henripittieri" order="Myrtales" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="henripittieri">
<emphasis id="57177F79D239392729EE53673A0C22CA" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">henripittieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was chosen for this species because 
<taxonomicName id="51875935A69F08FFFCFB8F0B33380B3F" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="pittieri" order="Myrtales" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pittieri">
<emphasis id="DFA890BD18F310734AB0B424F94F8410" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">pittieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is preempted by 
<taxonomicName id="140718F2889F6747C07D432863647C4E" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia pittieri" order="Myrtales" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pittieri">
<emphasis id="18C0B8136F52B1C178645C2AB59197EA" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">Conostegia pittieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cogn. ex T. Durand. 
<taxonomicName id="EF118E842142180B62875A1736FFE2FD" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia henripitteri" order="Myrtales" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="henripitteri">
<emphasis id="0027E185CB5D19693D5324ACFBD810A9" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">Conostegia henripitteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unmistakeable because of its glabrous, subsessile, anisophyllous leaves. Although I was not able to see flowering material of this species, the isotype at F shows the evidently exserted style that is almost universal in section 
<taxonomicName id="CC757EDC60B2AEF249879751A700D595" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis id="BB5ADA2A429CDBDC3022890FAE4E3FBD" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
